Package: CERMBweather
Title: Functions to manage and query Australian weather data
Version: 0.3.0
Date: 2020-11-03
Authors@R: c(
  person("Hamish", "Clarke", email = "hamishc@uow.edu.au", role = c("aut")),
  person("Meaghan", "Jenkins", email = "mjenkins@uow.edu.au", role = c("aut")),
  person("Michael", "Bedward", email = "michael.bedward@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")) )
Description: Tools developed by the Centre for Environmental Risk Management
  of Bushfires, University of Wollongong (Australia) to manage and query weather 
  data provided by the Australian Bureau of Meteorology, and to calculate fire and
  weather-related indices.
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
